JS**********************************
//while loop is just like a for loop but instead we need to declare i before hand and need to increment what ever we are doning at the end 
but before the closing of the while loop. As we can see "document.getElementById("mypar").innerHTML" is starting to look like the JS 
version of cout<<
var i = 0;
var name = ["Russell"];
while(i<5){
document.getElementById("mypar").innerHTML += "<br/>" + "ID: " + i + " Name: " + name;
i++;

}
